Description:
The Jewel Of Drysdale!
Do you desire the ultimate 'downsize' prospect? Perfectly positioned within one of Drysdale's premiere cul-de-sac's is this charming, character filled residence. A stunning tree lined street, quality homes as far as the eye can see, neighbouring parklands and a short stroll to Drysdale's fully equipped retail hub fully endorses the A+ location!
X2 generously proportioned bedrooms; master is complete with a trio of floor to ceiling built in robes and an ensuite
The primary living zone is a fine example of open plan design; an enviable northerly orientation is complemented by expansive windows which promote lovely filtered light and a front row seat to take in glorious established gardens
The kitchen serves up a wonderful space; there is absolutely no compromise on size and scale. Expansive benchtops and excellent storage solutions complement stainless steel appliances and quality fixtures
All the modern comforts; gas ducted heating, split system cooling, custom window furnishings and many more fine features to be discovered on further inspection
A prime land holding of 489m2 (approx) is enhanced by a stunning established garden setting; the corner allotment profile provides further user friendly qualities
A double remote controlled garage with internal access
The Bellarine Peninsula is a thriving market place; award winning wineries, a vibrant cafe and restaurant scene, fully equipped medical services, beautiful parklands and the tranquillity of the 'sea change' are all at 'arms reach' if you are lucky enough to secure the charming 1 Pascoe Place, Drysdale
Insights: 1 Pascoe Place, Drysdale VIC 3222 was last sold in 2019 and 10 other 2 bedroom house in Drysdale have recently been sold.

Drysdale Acreage
Located on the outskirts of Drysdale in a quality, rural residential estate. This one acre allotment sits on a slight slope.
Blank canvass is the best way to describe this cleared land.
Central to the Clifton Springs Boat Ramp for the avid fisherman, the Portarlington Ferry for that day trip to Melbourne, various wineries and cafes for a leisurely luncheon date, the shopping and commercial centre of Drysdale and the list goes on.
Services to the front of the block.
Call the agent for further details

Description:
Picture Perfect in the Heart of Drysdale
This beautiful family residence is equipped with all the elements that a growing family needs. Located in a desirable Drysdale pocket just moments to all the Drysdale amenities is simply a bonus of this picturesque home.
This inviting Crescent is tucked away in quiet and well presented no through Road. The picket fence and manicured establish gardens exude a warm and inviting entry.
Set across 2 levels, this practical and free flowing floor plan will ensure all members of the family have their space. The ground level is the heart of the home, welcomed with timber floors and adorned with ceiling roses, character fretwork and ¾ feature walls in the living room. Home to the family room with feature fire, study/ versatile 5th bedroom, an updated kitchen including gas cooking and stainless-steel appliances with views of the garden and overlooking the dining area with access out to the undercover area. The laundry and separate toilet complete the lower level. The first floor is home to 4 bedrooms, the master suite with walk-in robe and ensuite, the remaining 3 bedrooms all with robes (bedrooms 3 & 4 with Bay glimpses). A second living area, main bathroom and toilet complete the upper level.
The front and back gardens are manicured and established with plenty of room for the kids to run around. The double carport has a very handy and wide side access leading straight to the oversized double lock up garage.
Features include ducted heating, evaporative cooling, additional cooling unit, feature wall heater, roller blinds, an abundance of storage with character features throughout.
A charming home in a sought-after pocket that has been well maintained and ready for you to move into.

Description:
Prized Location, Premium Opportunity!
Enviably situated moments from the Drysdale Shopping Precinct, 2/38-40 Princess Street presents itself with all the hallmarks of what living in Central Drysdale has to offer.
Set securely back from the street, as one of only five townhouses, the opportunity for the astute investor or downsizer is not to be overlooked. Upon entering, you are greeted with superbly proportioned open plan living and dining rooms that feature vaulted 4.6m high ceilings, that gives this home a well-designed, spacious feel.
Featuring a stylish refurbished kitchen with a large pantry that overlooks the neat and compact courtyard area, two spacious bedrooms with built in robes and a centrally located bathroom, keen buyers will delight in this opportunity and see the home for its full potential.
The property is currently tenanted with a rental return of $315pw and a Residential Tenancy Agreement is in place until 20/01/2020. The additional bonus to this home is that you are within easy walking distance to all that central Drysdale has to offer.
With its vast array of quality shops and cafes, access to bus services, moments to all the world class wineries and restaurants that the Bellarine Peninsula is renowned for, 2/38-40 Princess Street is a definite property to be put on your short list.

Description:
Lots Of Space To Grow
With the centre of town a short stroll away, this recently renovated Drysdale home has been given a new lease on life. On a generous corner allotment it has the capacity for a further makeover with an extension (STCA) or live comfortably as it is or secure as a tidy investment.
Upon entry is a l-shaped living and dining area with a kitchen equipped with a Fisher & Paykel dishwasher and stand alone oven. Outside is a large north-facing yard and deck that is ideal for entertaining and providing space for children and pets to play.
Follow the hallway to three good-size bedrooms, two with built-in robes, a modern central bathroom, laundry and separate toilet. Also attached to the property is a bungalow with possibilities for a home office, fourth bedroom or teenagers retreat.
There is a single lock-up garage and workshop to keep the handyperson happy and ample room for parking additional vehicles or trailers.
Walk to shops, schools, parks, cafes and amenities with easy access to the highway into Geelong. Book an inspection today!

Description:
Settle in to Leisure and Lifestyle
There is a Zen like quality to this family friendly home in a quiet court location. From the subtle earthy décor to the 801sqm (approx) sunny landscaped gardens, the vibe is relaxed and welcoming. You will love the layout and the smart design that makes the most of the northerly aspect.
The master suite is positioned away from the main living zone and the three additional generously sized bedrooms. It is spacious and includes a walk in robe and en-suite. The nearby sitting room offers a quiet zone to wind down in and would make an ideal parents retreat away from the hustle of family life. The open plan living, kitchen and dining is the central hub of the home and this is where everyday living and entertaining happens with ease. A super functional kitchen boasts great storage and workspace, stainless appliances and a breakfast bar. There is effortless flow to sheltered outdoor living through large sliding doors, making BBQs and enjoying summer evenings with family and friends a breeze.
As well as an internal access double lock up garage, the property includes an extra freestanding double garage. This added bonus offers additional parking for the boat or trailer and it is perfect as a workshop or creative space while adding to the already generous storage options.
This desirable location is ideal for reaping the benefits of life on the Bellarine. Just a short commute to Geelong, it is also centrally placed for access to the fabulous rail trail, local shops, nature reserves, bay side and world-class ocean beaches as well as community and sporting facilities. Solid and low maintenance, this home is an obvious choice for anyone wanting leisure, lifestyle and peaceful family living.

Description:
Serene Estate
A lifestyle opportunity enabling you to thrive and prosper in an intimate residential estate. Residing in this enviable location offers a lifestyle of coastal living, the convenience of a large regional centre within a 20 minute drive and designed around a semi rural, close knit community with every convenience at your doorstep.
The peninsula location is renowned for the idyllic, outdoor lifestyle. Spend a day at the beach, go fishing or enjoy a glass of your favourite wine at one of our many local wineries. The Port Phillip Ferry sails twice daily from Portarlington to South Bank if you fancy a day trip to the city. You will ask yourself why you didn't make the move sooner.
Ground works to commence late 2018.
Selling fast, contact Rhonda Humpage 0457 313609

GREAT LOCATION

Description:
SOUGHT AFTER QUIET COURT
Located in a tightly held, quiet court location in Drysdale is this delightful three bedroom home. This residence has a spacious open plan living space with the kitchen overlooking two light filled living areas, a study/play room (with scope to be converted into a fourth bedroom if required) and secure, private rear yard. The roomy master bedroom has an ensuite and shelved WIR and the remaining two bedrooms have built in robes. With gas ducted heating, split system air conditioning, a spa bath, a fresh coat of paint and too many features to list - this property really needs to be seen to be appreciated. So whether you are a retiree, family, new home buyer or investor book an inspection today.
What do you know about this historic town of Drysdale or the immediate area? Do you need to get to Melbourne to work? The ferry from Portarlington to Docklands is only 10 minutes down the road with no problem parking the car for the day. The choice of the many wineries, restaurants and even a whiskery means that socialising with family and friends will find you never running out of places to visit and try.
Drysdale itself is currently undergoing some major progress changes with the Bypass well under way for a mid-2020 completion.
Schooling in the area offers Public, Catholic and Christian primary and secondary options. With a population well balanced between families and retirees the community gels very well together.
Our SpringDale Neighbourhood Centre will answer all your new to the area questions. Everything you need to survive day to day is here in this place.

Description:
Dreaming of a Rural Lifestyle
If you have been dreaming of a rural lifestyle but would still like the close proximity to the coast, schools and shops, then this is what you have been waiting for. Tucked away on the outskirts of Drysdale on the Bellarine Peninsula, this picturesque property features an expansive sugar gum plantation and the remainder of the property contains majestic gum trees, wattles and an assortment of native flora and fauna as well as two dams. Set on Approx 10 hectares (Approx 25 Acres), there is the potential to build your own dream home or resurrect, renovate and extend the original Miners cottage. This property offers the best of both worlds. The large acreage gives you the feeling of being away from it all, but within minutes you can be on the beach, in Geelong or on the ferry to Melbourne. Zoned farming, the area is renowned for its fertile soil and there is plenty of scope for horse agistment and other hobby farming possibilities. Close by are several of the regions award winning wineries, restaurants and the Curlewis Golf Club. An idyllic lifestyle is guaranteed.

Description:
X Factor!
Without a moment of doubt this executive residence announces itself as one of the finest in the local property market! Stylish, sophisticated and showcasing an inclusions list of the highest calibre it is a must see for prospective purchasers who demand uncompromising excellence! A fine example of a contemporary open plan design is complemented by highly desirable lifestyle features delivering the ultimate 'seachange' experience!
Beautifully appointed 4 bedroom home; the luxurious master suite is complete with expansive bay window feature, ensuite and walk in robe
The primary living zone consists of an open plan kitchen/family/dining zone, it is bathed in an abundance of natural light; wonderful use of expansive windows creates a lovely inside/outside connection to the stunning garden/pool setting
The kitchen is 'top shelf' in every sense; sleek contemporary straight lines work seamlessly with earthy textures and tones. Expansive dual stone benchtops (50mm waterfall effect), custom cabinetry, feature tile splashback, Asko integrated dishwasher, Smeg stainless steel gas cook top and the user friendly design brief is sure to impress
A 2nd and 3rd living zone provides further flexibility to what is already a very adaptable floor plan
This fine residence will excite 'the entertainer' within; a beautifully appointed decked alfresco with a striking gable roof provides a great vantage spot to take in the landscaped gardens 'or' keep a watchful eye over the kids playing in the pool
All the modern comforts including gas ducted heating and evaporative cooling; an impressive inclusions list and key liveability features ensure this home is winning the efficiency stakes (solar panels etc)
A prime land holding of 684m2 (approx) is tastefully landscaped with an emphasis on low maintenance; established fruit trees, raised garden beds, established turf all complement the tranquillity of a truly eye catching pool setting (fully equipped)
The A+++ location simply cannot be overstated; positioned right in the heart of a boutique pocket of Drysdale. Surrounded by impressive quality homes and perfectly placed to have all of Drysdale's amenities at arms reach (schools, medical services, fully equipped retail sector and a vibrant cafe/restaurant scene. The Bellarine Peninsula is a thriving market place; award winning wine labels, beautiful parklands, excellent boating and fishing prospects and the panoramic views of the bay.

Description:
Contemporary Low Maintenance Living
Cute, quaint and contemporary, this Long Island Home build is positioned perfectly within the ever-popular boutique Central Walk Estate. Neat as a pin and immaculately presented, there is nothing left to do but simply move in and enjoy the lifestyle on offer.
The charm is felt imminently upon entry, with inviting timber floating floors and a clean crisp neutral palette. Bedrooms 1 and 2 sit at the fore of the home from the central hallway, are spacious in size and both comprise built-in-robes. The master retreat sits centrally and hosts a walk-in-robe and fully equipped ensuite with toilet, vanity and shower. A truly unique aspect from the master is also on offer, with sliding door access to a private and sun-filled courtyard -The most perfect place to enjoy that morning cup of tea! The lavish central bathroom offers stone benchtop vanity, tiled in bath, shower, a separate toilet and nifty laundry with storage and outdoor side access completes this wing of the home. The designer kitchen offers 40mm stone benchtops, 900ml gas cooking, stainless steel dishwasher, walk-in-pantry and an abundance of storage, all while overlooking the open plan dining and living area. Sliding door access from the dining welcomes you to a neat undercover area, which wraps around to an open grassed space. Complete with a SLUG with internal and external access and situated upon a nifty 306m2 block, low maintenance living has never looked so good!
Conveniently located with supermarkets, shops, public transport and schools only a short stroll away and with Golf Courses, the Bay, boat ramp, wineries, eateries and beaches and all that The Bellarine has to offer at your fingertips! The perfect opportunity to secure a unique home in a highly sought after location.

Description:
GRAND AND ELEGANT FAMILY ABODE
Situated in the heart of Drysdale, this superb family home has been built with pride and sits gracefully on approx. 1273m2 parcel of land overlooking lush green fields. This extensive home features multiple living spaces on a grand scale including a unique central atrium courtyard, a delightful formal lounge with ornamental fireplace, open plan kitchen, meals, family room and a parents retreat upstairs with balcony. French doors are featured throughout the home leading onto multiple balconies, with the main outdoor entertaining area flowing out from the open plan living room and kitchen. The upstairs Master bedroom is spacious and features WIR and full size ensuite and enjoys access to the upstairs living area and central atrium, giving natural light through the home. 3 further bedrooms with BIR's and home office contribute to the size and elegance of this home. An enormous 6 car garage underneath the home has to be seen to be appreciated and can easily accommodate multiple cars, a large boat and a full sized caravan.
